@jaraco you are right in that there isn't much point implementing it in-process, although an atexit handler that does garbage collection would at least ensure expired ones could be removed some of the time.  Possibly also do the same on opening a keyring.

I'm considering the Linux desktop environment where keyring (I assume) is using Secret Service over dbus.  Whatever is implementing Secret Service can then do the garbage collection, as well as respecting time to live.  I believe that is something like Gnome Keyring.  

In terms of API, all I'd want is a time to live parameter on the keyring.set_password method.  If the backend has proper time to live support then use that.  If not then something like my first paragraph (library manually  garbage collecting/expiring).

