@xiamx yes that makes sense. I think pthreads can be supported if subsytem is set to `POSIX (/SUBSYSTEM:POSIX)` under project > linker > system settings.

Last note, without pthreads flag I was worried if multiple threads are actually utilized or not with resulting executable, but they are:

![fasttext_multithreads](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/32342269/35031719-2d840256-fb75-11e7-9666-04a46b043fb4.png)
  
In this use case I set the `-thread` flag to be 20.

> If this whole proposal sounds good, this might also be a good time to consider moving user-defined casters out of the `detail` namespace.

+1 for making type casters "public", I've written my good share of custom type casters and it always feels a bit wrong to specialize things in `pybind11::detail` namespace in downstream code. Plus, doing this provides an option to deprecate the old `detail` type casters more gracefully at the same time.

----

A bit of bikeshedding:

```cpp
static maybe<U> load(handle src, bool convert) {
    if (auto maybe_value = make_caster<T>::load(src, convert))
        return maybe_value.extract<T>();
    return {};
}
```

could even be

```cpp
static maybe<U> load(handle src, bool convert) {
    return make_caster<T>::load(src, convert).try_extract<T>();
}
```

if it's a common pattern.

